# Data sources + safety conventions

- **Maps**: Leaflet + OSM tiles.
- **Geocoding**: Nominatim (be gentle; cache where possible; set UA).
- **Weather**: Open‑Meteo forecast; if outside horizon, show **historical reference** with year.
- **Routing**: OSRM (free) via backend proxy endpoints; clear old routes on day changes.
- **Restaurants**: Overpass API; explain source clearly in UI; keyword filtering + fallback queries.
- **Safe links**:
  - only render clickable links for `https://` URLs
  - use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` + `target="_blank"`
  - avoid embedding external sites; most block iframes and it bloats UI
- **Persistence**:
  - shared compendium/staging stored server-side (`data/*.json`)
  - per-user UI state stored client-side (localStorage) when appropriate
